          <para styleclass="Popup Box">A <text styleclass="VariableName-small">Bell-Crank</text> is a <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Part</text> that is usually connected to the <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Base-Part</text> with a <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Pin-Joint</text><image src="Red-14-2.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"></image><text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">. </text></para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">Two more <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Pin-Joints</text><image src="Red-14-3.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"></image><image src="Red-14-5.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"></image> at two other <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Points</text> to create a two levers<image src="Red-14-1.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"></image><image src="Red-14-4.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"></image>.</para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">The lengths of the levers define if the <text styleclass="VariableName-small">Bell-Crank</text> amplifies or attenuates the motion. </para>
